div1.p:
JOHN BROWN. I keep the Cheshunt errand cart
. I had my cart at Mr. Jermer's door, (the Orange-tree public-house, Bloomsbury


), on the 11th of January, and had a box in it which I had got from Harriet Westley, of Cheshunt. I left the cart at the door about eleven o'clock, returned in about twenty-five minutes, and found the box in possession of the officer.
